thread.title: Locals in the NFL roundup for week five: Orchard shines; Davis out for year
thread.title_full: Locals in the NFL roundup for week five: Orchard shines; Davis out for year | Deseret News

author: Brandon Gurney
title: Locals in the NFL roundup for week five: Orchard shines; Davis out for year
text:
Former Utah Ute Nate Orchard had a big game while former Utah State Aggie Will Davis suffered a season-ending ACL injury.
• Maurice Alexander, DB, Utah State, St. Louis Rams, was inactive in St. Louis' 24-10 loss to the Green Bay Packers.
• Dres Anderson, WR, Utah, San Francisco 49ers, was inactive in San Fransisco's 30-27 loss to the New York Giants.
• Ezekiel Ansah, DE, BYU, Detroit Lions, had a solo tackle for a loss, a sack and two quarterback hits in Detroit's 42-17 loss to the Arizona Cardinals.
• Matt Asiata, RB, Hunter HS, Utah, Minnesota Vikings, had a bye in week five.
• Zane Beadles, OL, Hillcrest HS, Utah, Jacksonville Jaguars, started at left guard during Jacksonville's 38-31 loss to the Jacksonville Jaguars.
• Tony Bergstrom, OL, Skyline HS, Utah, Oakland Raiders, was listed as his team's backup center during Oakland's 16-10 loss to the Denver Broncos.
• Sam Brenner, OL, Utah, Miami Dolphins, had a bye in week five.
• Will Davis, DB, Utah State, Baltimore Ravens, suffered a season-ending torn ACL injury during Baltimore's 33-30 loss to the Cleveland Browns.
• John Denney, DS, BYU, Miami Dolphins, had a bye in week five.
• Jordan Devey, OL, Memphis, American Fork HS, San Francisco 49ers, started at right guard during his team's 30-27 loss to the New York Giants.
• Alani Fua, LB, BYU, Arizona Cardinals, had a quarterback hit during Arizona's 42-17 win over the Detroit Lions.
• Paul Kruger, OLB, Timpanogos HS, Utah, Cleveland Browns, did not record a stat during Cleveland's 33-30 win over the Baltimore Ravens.
• Nevin Lawson, DB, Utah State, Detroit Lions, had a solo tackle in Detroit's 42-17 loss to the Arizona Cardinals.
• Star Lotulelei, DL, Bingham HS, Utah, Carolina Panthers, had a bye in week five.
• Keith McGill, S, Utah, Oakland Raiders, did not record a stat in Oakland's 16-10 loss to the Denver Broncos.
• Koa Misi, OLB, Utah, Miami Dolphins, had a bye in week five.
• Haloti Ngata, DT, Highland HS and Oregon, Detroit Lions, was inactive due to injury in Detroit's 42-17 loss to the Arizona Cardinals.
• Nate Orchard, OLB, Highland HS and Utah, Cleveland Browns, had five tackles, four of them solo, and defended a pass in Cleveland's 33-30 win over the Baltimore Ravens.
• Stephen Paea, DT, Timpview HS and Oregon State, Washington Redskins, had a solo tackle and a quarterback hit in Washington's 25-19 loss to the Atlanta Falcons.
• Donald Penn, OL, Utah State, Oakland Raiders, started at left tackle during Oakland's 16-10 loss to the Denver Broncos. He also caught a pass on a deflection and gained three yards on the play.
• Jeremiah Poutasi, OL, Utah, Tennessee Titans, started at right tackle in Tennessee's 14-13 loss to the Buffalo Bills.
• Trevor Reilly, OLB, Utah, New York Jets, had a bye in week five.
• Derrick Shelby, DE, Utah, Miami Dolphins, had a bye in week five.
• Sealver Siliga, DT, Copper Hills HS and Utah, New England Patriots, had four tackles, one of them solo, in New England's 30-6 win over the Dallas Cowboys.
• Alex Smith, QB, Utah, Kansas City Chiefs, went 16-30 through the air for 181 yards and a touchdown in Kansas City's 18-17 loss to the Chicago Bears. He also ran the ball three times for 21 yards.
